       ? Promise<Stubify<R> & MaybeDisposable<R>> & MaybeProvider<R>
-      : never;
+      // Cloudflare's generated RPC type currently collapses any return value that
+      // does not satisfy Rpc.Serializable<R> to never. That is too strict for
+      // Durable Object / Worker RPC methods that intentionally return opaque
+      // application data containing unknown, for example stream events with
+      // payload?: unknown. The runtime can still deliver that value, but the
+      // generated stub type becomes unusable.
+      // Upstream bug: https://github.com/cloudflare/workerd/issues/5200
+      // Local tracking: https://linear.app/iterate-com/issue/ITE-1728/fix-the-types-in-cloudflare-do-stubs
+      // Keep the promise/disposable shape so callers still see RPC lifecycle
+      // semantics while preserving the original application return type.
+      : Promise<R & MaybeDisposable<R>>;
   // Type for method or property on an RPC interface.
   // For methods, unwrap `Stub`s in parameters, and rewrite returns to be `Result`s.
   // Unwrapping `Stub`s allows calling with `Stubable` arguments.
